## Bucket Policy — Access Control

Block all public access by default (this is now the AWS default):

```bash
aws s3api put-public-access-block \
  --bucket my-app-bucket-joon \
  --public-access-block-configuration \
    "BlockPublicAcls=true,IgnorePublicAcls=true,BlockPublicPolicy=true,RestrictPublicBuckets=true"
```

Allow read from specific IAM role only:

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "AllowAppRoleRead",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::ACCOUNT_ID:role/ec2-app-role"
      },
      "Action": ["s3:GetObject", "s3:ListBucket"],
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::my-app-bucket-joon",
        "arn:aws:s3:::my-app-bucket-joon/*"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

```bash
aws s3api put-bucket-policy \
  --bucket my-app-bucket-joon \
  --policy file://bucket-policy.json
```

