## Static Website Hosting

```bash
# Enable website hosting
aws s3api put-bucket-website \
  --bucket my-site-bucket \
  --website-configuration '{
    "IndexDocument": {"Suffix": "index.html"},
    "ErrorDocument": {"Key": "404.html"}
  }'

# For a public site, you need to allow public reads
# (disable block public access first, then add bucket policy)
aws s3api put-bucket-policy \
  --bucket my-site-bucket \
  --policy '{
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": [{
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": "*",
      "Action": "s3:GetObject",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::my-site-bucket/*"
    }]
  }'

# Deploy your site
aws s3 sync ./build/ s3://my-site-bucket/ --delete

# Access at: http://my-site-bucket.s3-website.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com
```

For production, put CloudFront in front of S3 — it adds HTTPS, CDN caching, and custom domain support.

